page.title: 19LOCAL HISTORY 2
page.content: THE ITCHEN NAVIGATION CANAL. Dug between 1665 and 1710. It left the river at Mansbridge Lock and passing through 15 locks finishing at Winchester. Much of the canal has become impassable for{transport.} MANSBRIDGE FIRST & MIDDLE SCHOOL was built in 1960 on the site previously occupied by Grange Farm. The{school} provides primary{education}for children from the Swaythling{Housing} Society estate and is centrally situated. At the present time the staff consists of a Headteacher and Deputy Headteacher, 7 teachers, a secretary, a caretaker and 1 cleaner, 1 cook, 2 kitchen helpers and 4 dining room assistants, 1 part-time ancillary helper, 1 language and 3 peripatetic music teachers. There are 237 children.
